<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" Description="This CalDef is intended to contain Trailering Application related calibrations.">
  <CalDefFileVersion>10</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <Date>6/9/2016</Date>
    <Description>Initial release of Trailering Application related calibrations.</Description>
    <Author>Frank Bruneel</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>10/24/2016</Date>
    <Description>Within this caldef file added seven driver workload calibrations (PlusNewTrailerDriverWorkload, EditTrailerButtonDriverWorkload, PlusChecklistItemDriverWorkload, EditCustomChecklistItemDriverWorkload, EditMaintenanceReminderButtonDriverWorkload, PlusCustomReminderDriverWorkload, and SubviewofChecklistDriverWorkload) from the GIS-539</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>3/2/2017</Date>
    <Description>With the GIS539_TrailerAppUI.caldef file added the following nine new driver workload calibrations to support RTC CR#: 1337272: 1.) TrailerDetectedDriverWorkload, 2.) DiagnoseDriverWorkload, 3.) StartLightTestDriverWorkload, 4.) PlusNewMaintenanceReminderDriverWorkload, 5.) TirePressureSetupDriverWorkload, 6.) EditMileageDriverWorkload, 7.) ChecklistDriverWorkload, 8.) GuestTrailerDriverWorkload, and 9.) Tow_HaulLearnDriverWorkload. Also, updated the default value of the following six driver workload calibrations: 1.) PlusChecklistItemDriverWorkload, 2.)EditCustomChecklistItemDriverWorkload, 3.) EditMaintenanceReminderButtonDriverWorkload, 4.) PlusCustomReminderDriverWorkload, 5.) EditTrailerButtonDriverWorkload, and 6.) PlusNewTrailerDriverWorkload calibrations from a default value of LowSpeed = Trigger Level Value of 2  to Medium Speed = Trigger Level Value of 3 to match the default value update shown in the latest version GIS-539 for these calibrations.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>3/7/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS539_TrailerAppUI.caldef, added usage of Low Radio for the TraileringAppType calibration, now that it is confirmed this calibration is also needed for Low Radio.  This also reflects the usage shown in the latest GIS-739 Spec. </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
    <Description>Updated the usage field for all of the calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>9/26/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS539_TrailerAppUI.caldef file added the following twenty one calibrations added to the GIS-539 for MY20 under CR#:  1108899: 1.) TRAILER_HEIGHT_MAX, 2.) TRAILER_HEIGHT_MIN,  3.) OVERLAY_MAX_LENGTH, 4.) TRAILER_CAMERA_ANGLE, 5.) CAMERA_ADJUSTMENT_AMOUNT,  6.) TRAILER_MIN_WIDTH, 7.) TRAILER_MAX_WIDTH, 8.) TRAILER_MIN_HITCHING_LENGTH,  9.) TRAILER_MAX_HITCHING_LENGTH, 10.) TRAILER_MIN_LENGTH,  11.) TRANSPARENT_TRAILER_MAX_LENGTH, 12.) POSITION_CAMERA_INSTRUCTIONS, 13.) TRAILER_OVERLAY, 14.) TRANSPARENT_TRAILER_FEATURE, 15.) JACKKNIFE_FEATURE, 16.) ADJUST_CAMERA_POSITION, 17.) TrailerLengthOverlayDriverWorkload,  18.) TrailerLengthOverlaySettingDriverWorkload, 19.) CalibrationUnsuccessfulDriverWorkload, 20.) SetUpViewDriverWorkload, and 21.) EnterTrailerDimensionsDriverWorkload. Also within the GIS539_TrailerAppUI.caldef  file, added GEM usage to the TraileringAppType calibration. Since it fell within the current criteria of requiring GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>05/03/2018</Date>
    <Description>For MY21 per CR#:996123, CR#1340146, CR#1340019, CR#1337594, and CR#1777319, added the following seven calibrations within the GIS-539_TrailerAppUI.caldef: 1) REAR_TRAILER_GUIDELINES_ENABLED 2) LOAD_MONITORING_ENABLED 3) ESBZA_FEATURE_ENABLED 4) VEHICLE_TYPE 5) WeightLimitLearnMoreDriverWorkload 6) LoadRatingsDriverWorkload 7) LoadViewIssueDriverWorkload</Description>
    <Author>Emmanuel Oleka</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>8</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>9</Version>
    <Date>9/28/2020</Date>
    <Description>Per CR#2640865, adding new cal GCWR</Description>
    <Author>Greg Lindemann</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>10</Version>
    <Date>11/03/2020</Date>
    <Description>Per CR#2337061 made the following updates within the GIS539_TrailerAppUI.caldef file: Added the following 2 cals: 1.) INTERIOR_TRAILER_CAMERA_ENABLED and 2.) REAR_TRAILER_CAMERA_ENABLED</Description>
    <Author>Greg Lindemann</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="This cal is used to determine whether the Rear Trailer Camera feature will be enabled or disabled.  True = Rear Trailer Camera HMI will appear.  False = Rear Trailer Camera HMI will not appear" Name="REAR_TRAILER_CAMERA_ENABLED" References="CR#2337061 - MFL955_23MY Updated scope BT1XX Trailering App Experience" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALB">
    <CalID>_W6lMEB4vEeuVRpAUhp1aqw</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>11/03/2020</Date>
      <Description>Initial release of this calibration</Description>
      <Author>Greg Lindemann</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>false</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="This cal is used to determine whether the Interior Trailer Camera feature will be enabled or disabled.  True = Interior Trailer Camera HMI will appear.  False = Interior Trailer Camera HMI will not appear" Name="INTERIOR_TRAILER_CAMERA_ENABLED" References="CR#2337061 - MFL955_23MY Updated scope BT1XX Trailering App Experience" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALB">
    <CalID>_wRZKsB4sEeuVRpAUhp1aqw</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>11/03/2020</Date>
      <Description>Initial release of this calibration</Description>
      <Author>Greg Lindemann</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>false</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="GCWR is the total allowable weight of the completely loaded vehicle and trailer including any fuel, passengers, cargo, equipment, and accessories." Name="GCWR" References="Trailering App System Decomposition - 2.3.1.7" Usage="MID,HIGH,VCU,GLOBALA,GLOBALB">
